# SCSS Structure and Styling Conventions

## File Organization

### Theme Structure
```
src/scss/
├── default/           # Main theme (active)
│   ├── _variables.scss      # Color & sizing variables
│   ├── _variables-dark.scss # Dark mode variables
│   ├── _functions.scss      # SCSS utility functions
│   ├── _mixins.scss         # Reusable mixins
│   ├── app/                 # App-specific styles
│   ├── layout/              # Layout components
│   ├── ui/                  # UI components
│   └── styles.scss          # Main import file
├── apple/             # Alternative theme
├── facebook/          # Alternative theme
├── google/            # Alternative theme
├── material/          # Alternative theme
└── transparent/       # Alternative theme
```

### Component Styles
```
src/app/
├── features/          # Feature-specific styles
│   └── [feature]/
│       └── [feature].scss
└── shared/            # Shared component styles
    └── [component]/
        └── [component].scss
```

## Variable Usage

### Always Use Variables
❌ **Bad**: `background: #1b76ff;`
✅ **Good**: `background: var(--bs-app-theme);`

❌ **Bad**: `color: #3ddc84;`
✅ **Good**: `color: var(--bs-success);`

### Theme Variables
- `var(--bs-app-theme)` - Primary theme color
- `var(--bs-app-theme-color)` - Text color on theme background
- `var(--bs-app-header-bg)` - Header background
- `var(--bs-app-sidebar-bg)` - Sidebar background

### Color Variables
- `var(--bs-primary)` - Blue
- `var(--bs-success)` - Green
- `var(--bs-warning)` - Orange
- `var(--bs-danger)` - Red
- `var(--bs-info)` - Cyan

## Naming Conventions

### BEM Methodology
Use BEM (Block Element Modifier) for component classes:
```scss
.stat-card {              // Block
  &__title { }           // Element
  &__value { }           // Element
  &--primary { }         // Modifier
  &--info { }            // Modifier
}
```

### Semantic Class Names
- Use descriptive names that explain purpose, not appearance
- ❌ `.blue-box` ✅ `.notification-card`
- ❌ `.big-text` ✅ `.heading-primary`

## Best Practices

### 1. Nesting
- Limit nesting to 3 levels maximum
- Use `&` for pseudo-classes and modifiers
```scss
.component {
  &:hover { }
  &.active { }
  
  &__element {
    &--modifier { }
  }
}
```

### 2. Responsiveness
Use Bootstrap breakpoint mixins:
```scss
@include media-breakpoint-down(md) {
  // Mobile styles
}

@include media-breakpoint-up(lg) {
  // Desktop styles
}
```

### 3. Transitions
Always add smooth transitions:
```scss
transition: all 0.3s ease;
// or specific properties
transition: background-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
```

### 4. Z-Index
Use defined z-index variables from `_variables.scss`:
- `$app-header-zindex: 1020`
- `$app-sidebar-zindex: 1010`
- `$app-theme-panel-zindex: 1035`

### 5. Spacing
Use rem-based spacing from variables:
```scss
padding: $spacer;                    // Base spacing
margin-bottom: $spacer * 2;          // Double spacing
gap: rem(15px);                      // Custom rem conversion
```

